#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
msgid "Mt. 4:4"
msgstr "Matt. 4:4"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
msgid ""
"nourishment -- \"But He answered and said, 'It is written, Man shall not "
"live on bread alone, but on every word that proceeds out of the mouth of "
"God.'\""
msgstr ""
"næring -- \"Men han svarede: Der står skrevet: ›Mennesket skal ikke leve af "
"brød alene, men af hvert ord, der udgår af Guds mund.‹\""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><title>
msgid "A Book that Liberates"
msgstr "En bog som befrier"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><para>
msgid ""
"Jn.8:32 \" <emphasis>and you shall know the truth, and the truth shall make "
"you free.</emphasis>\"This is usually quoted by itself. Is this a "
"conditional or unconditional promise? Would it apply to all kinds of "
"knowledge? Find the answers by examining the first half of the sentence, in "
"v.31. \" <emphasis>If you abide in My word, then you are truly disciples of "
"Mine...</emphasis>\""
msgstr ""
"Joh.8:32 \" <emphasis>og I skal kende sandheden, og sandheden skal gøre "
"jer frie.</emphasis>\" Dette citeres normalt alene. Er det et betinget "
"eller ubetinget løfte? Gælder det alle slags kundskab? Find svarene ved "
"at undersøge første halvdel af sætningen, i v.31. \" <emphasis>Hvis I "
"bliver i mit ord, er I sandelig mine disciple...</emphasis>\""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><para>
msgid ""
"We see that this is a conditional promise, specifically speaking of the "
"truth of God's word."
msgstr ""
"Vi ser, at dette er et betinget løfte, som specifikt handler om "
"sandheden i Guds ord."

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><para>
msgid ""
"The Greek word for \"wind\" used in Eph.4:14 means a <emphasis>violent wind."
"</emphasis>\" <emphasis>As a result, we are no longer to be children, tossed "
"here and there by waves, and carried about by every wind of doctrine...</"
"emphasis>\"One thing studying the Bible does for us is to ground us in the "
"truth, with the result that we won't be easily \"blown away.\""
msgstr ""
"Det græske ord for \"vind\" i Ef.4:14 betyder en <emphasis>voldsom "
"vind.</emphasis>\" <emphasis>Så skal vi ikke længere være børn, der "
"kastes og drives hid og did af hver lærdoms vind...</emphasis>\" Én ting "
"bibelstudium gør for os, er at grundfæste os i sandheden, så vi ikke "
"let bliver \"blæst omkuld.\""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><sect1><para>
msgid ""
"<emphasis>But Jesus answered and said to them,</emphasis>\" <emphasis>You "
"are mistaken [KJV Ye do err], not understanding the Scriptures, or the power "
"of God.</emphasis>\" Mt.22:29"
msgstr ""
"<emphasis>Men Jesus svarede og sagde til dem:</emphasis>\" <emphasis>I "
"farer vild [KJV Ye do err], fordi I hverken kender Skrifterne eller "
"Guds kraft.</emphasis>\" Mt.22:29"

